{
  "stem": "10588.7",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In his right gloved hand, he holds a trenchant and points it, sometimes to the right, and sometimes to the left, selecting who shall live and who shall die.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He's a-- he is a Nazi murderer in snow white gloves, a university educated man with two doctoral degrees.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He's the infamous Dr.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Josef Mengele, Birkenau's angel of death.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He knows how to heal the sick, but perversely chooses to kill healthy Jews enslaved in the killing center of Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "More than 400,000 innocent men, women, and little children died at his hands.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And among them, unfortunately, my entire family of blessed memory was murdered on November 22nd, 1942 in the gas chambers of Auschwitz.'",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I saw Mengele on numerous occasions.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because they used to do [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "OK?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They also used to do selections.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH] means since we didn't get a change of clothes, we were wearing constantly the same clothes, so they would take-- take these clothes and put them to get the-- what calls?-- disinfect them.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "OK?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But also, he came to make selections.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He selected, you know, who should go to the gas chambers many times.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He selected people for experiments.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "When Mengele arrived, we all died inside by inches.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "By that time, I-- we knew who he was, the beginning.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this is what troubled me much more, because if they were barbarians, but they were educated people.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this is why I started to question everything.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I said, so what is education if it leads to Auschwitz?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "What is religion?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "People who are religious-- people-- Mengele from what I read about him later came from a fine family, was well educated, had degree.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So what do you put faith in?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So this is-- this is-- it tore up my whole belief system.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
